<br>
My guild was raiding Kedge, as a sort of expeditionary thing since none of us had tackled this dungeon before, and I got tell after tell for ports to GFay.  I sent out a guildsay tell people to gather ar wizzie ports for pick up (since druids were doing the same) and I would ferry and bind as I could.  We get everyone gathered and I get this:<br>
<br>
Guildee:  I need a pick up, had to handle some business.<br>
Me: OK, where are you?<br>
Guildee: Qeynos<br>
Me:  Can you meet me at the WK pyramid and then we'll pop right over?<br>
Guildee:  Sure!<br>
<br>
I get to WK pyramid and wait around then ask the Guildee for an ETA since the raid is getting started.<br>
<br>
Guildee: can you meet me in QHills?  I had to drop somethings off onto another account.<br>
Me:  You're kidding, right?<br>
Guildee:  No, it's gonna take me a few more minutes<br>
<br>
This person has SoW, I do not, but i go there anyway and pick them up get em over to Kedge (they got lost twice getting there) and then the person wants to take over and asks me if I really should be going along...<br>
<br>
No ports for you! <p>Severine <BR>
High Elf Wizard<BR>
Thank you for flying Air Severine and remember, your seat cushion may be used as a flotation device<BR>
:)</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=banzifsolro>Banzif SolRo</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(1/16/01 7:19:08 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I'm NOT a Bleepin Taxi!</span><hr size=1> If it is not a CR.<br>
I dont port many , if any, from anywhere but a PORTAL.<br>
in some cases i do, yesterday i wanted to be shown something<br>
and the person that knew was in KC, so I ran to the castel<br>
<br>
Imagine that you want somthing, you do something to get it done<br>
if people remembered that , at times things would go much eaiser. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uajeroth.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ajeroth</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(1/16/01 11:35:11 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I'm NOT a Bleepin Taxi!</span><hr size=1> Same. I will only do ports from:<br>
<br>
1. My current location.<br>
2. My bind point<br>
3. Wiz portals<br>
<br>
As a credit to my guild, I have never been asked to do otherwise. I have neither SoW, Selos, nor jboots. Other folks can do the running if I'm willing give the mana and the time to do the port. <p><img src="http://members.bellatlantic.net/~ogren/aj_logo.gif"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uizlaaru.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Izlaaru</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(1/17/01 4:30:54 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I'm NOT a Bleepin Taxi!</span><hr size=1> I'm much the same way.. but only time I'll run to a place is usually Karnor cause it's an Evac point to EJ/Skyfire.  And that's only for guildmates/friends.  Other than that if they aren't sitting on top of me or at a wizard portal I say &quot;Uh NO!&quot; or something to that effect. <p><BR><BR><font color="#FF0000" size="4"><A href="http://members.home.com/candon" target="_blank"><B><I>Izlaaru al'Tara</I></B></A></font><BR>
Daugther and High Priestess of Solusek Ro<BR>
