Heiress to the God of Flame
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=accolade>Accolade</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(1/27/01 11:41:48 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> re</span><hr size=1> Yea, i make people run to the porters.  I learned very quickly to just tell people if i was busy.  And then when i DO give a port i tell them to <br>
<br>
/t soandso Give me a tell when you get to the porter<br>
<br>
And if you're not a guildie or a friend you will be lining my moneypouch with some plat.  Not 10 plat either, i can do better by killing a single mob and taking his cash.  Clerics get paid a hundred plat for the service of saving players their time, why shouldn't i get something?  Especially since my res money for clerics has to come from somewhere :P<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=bryek>Bryek</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(1/30/01 1:40:33 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> peridots</span><hr size=1> BTW, most clerics prefer peridots to pp.<br>
<br>
It saves them the time of running to get them, and Sol Ro knows they need em. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ufaeadari.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Faeadari</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_fire.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(1/31/01 10:02:58 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.geocities.com/faeadari/fae5.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> porting</span><hr size=1> Some of the more interesting requests-<br>
