	</TR>
</TABLE></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ulordbug.showPublicProfile?language=EN>LordBug</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(2/7/01 11:14:07 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: porting</span><hr size=1> I'm permanently /role now.  Just got sick of it.  I was constantly asked for ports to places, and the requester wasn't even in the same zone.  I quite often would get requests from people in EC, FP, NRo for teleports to SRo.  Er... why?  I do still open up shop at Karnor's sometimes to do ports &quot;for donations&quot;.<br>
<br>
As for crossing Dreadlands, that's simple and safe.  I do still suggest Levitate (you do stock bat wings right?) and SOW/JBoots.  There's usually at least one druid at the druid ring in DL (east of wiz spires) too.  The only time I've ever been attacked was in the ice tunnel.  Beyond that, I just run right down the middle and straight to Karnor's.  If you do it right, you can get on top of Karnor's too (nothing to see, but it's fun).<br>
<br>
I, personally, hate teleporting to Iceclad (I have to get the other portals....).  Those damn dervishes are hell to deal with. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ulimdul.showPublicProfile?language=EN>LimDul</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Channeler</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(2/7/01 1:43:25 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.lava.net/~toasty/pictures/limdul.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: porting</span><hr size=1> Have I just been real lucky?  The dervishes at Iceclad haven't given me any problems...I only got attacked once but it was so green I simply ignored it and ran on.<br>
<br>
I'm just worried I'm ignorant about something at that portal, everybody's saying how bad it is.<br>
<br>
-- Lim'Dul <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=bryek>Bryek</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(2/7/01 2:18:15 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> portals</span><hr size=1> I've never had a problem with the dervishes.  Might be an issue to the low level wizards who just got the spell though. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/urazlik.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Razlik</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(2/7/01 5:55:43 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: portals</span><hr size=1> The iceclad portal is quite dangerous when you first get it. Snow dervishes pop through the walls there all the time. I assume frost giant scouts could be at the portal too, but I've never seen one right at the portal in 40-50 trips there.<br>
<br>
The two primary dangers are zone-lag (I zoned in with 2 bubbles of health left and a dervish beating on me one time thanks to zoning lag... thank goodness I had Steelskin up or I'd have zoned in with half a bubble =P) and group members who insist on stopping to fight whatever jumps them (which means you get to fight half the dervishes in the zone, it seems like =).<br>
<br>
...err back on topic...<br>
<br>
My favorite port request ever was when I was in EK talking to some small guildies, watching them whack gnolls, etc and got a tell from a guy (in zone) who needed a port to NK. I told him that NK was one zone away and he replied that he REALLY needed a port. I just about fell off my chair laughing....<br>
<br>
(It turned out that this guy actually DID need some help, because he'd been killing Muddites in the Gorge and collecting the clay... he was *crawling* and would have died if a gorge hound or something caught him on the way to the vendor...hee hee. I got him a strength buff from a guildie. =)<br>
<br>
My least favorite ports are the ones where you drop what you're doing because it's an EMERGENCY, port one or more snerts wearing gear you've never even heard of before, and then get zilch for your trouble. This used to happen to me a lot; I've fixed it now, though.<br>
<br>
Anyone who cannot spell the word &quot;you&quot; when asking for a port is automatically denied. My clientele is now MUCH more pleasant (and much more likely to pay me something for the lift).<br>
<br>
Snert: plz u port me 2 NK plz?<br>
Me: Sorry, I'm busy!<br>
Snert: ur not ur sittn ther<br>
Me: Sorry, I'm busy!<br>
Snert: i pay 100pp<br>
Me: *snort* Sorry, I'm busy!<br>
<br>
